  "cooking_instructions": [
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Preheat the oven to 220°C/ 200°C (fan)/ gas 7</p><p>Peel and cut your <strong>sweet potato[es]</strong> into fries</p>",
      "order": 1,
      "image": "/images/instructions/buffalo-halloumi-with-ranch-dip-and-sweet-potato-fries/step-1.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Add the <strong>sweet potato fries</strong> to a baking tray (or two!) with a drizzle of <strong>vegetable oil</strong> and a pinch of <strong>salt</strong></p><p>Give everything a good mix up and put the tray[s] in the oven for 20-25 min or until golden and crisp</p>",
      "order": 2,
      "image": "/images/instructions/buffalo-halloumi-with-ranch-dip-and-sweet-potato-fries/step-2.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>While the fries are cooking, cut your <strong>halloumi</strong> into 4 slices per person</p>",
      "order": 3,
      "image": "/images/instructions/buffalo-halloumi-with-ranch-dip-and-sweet-potato-fries/step-3.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Heat a large, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick) with a drizzle of <strong>vegetable oil</strong> over a medium-high heat</p><p>Once hot, add the <strong>sliced halloumi</strong> and cook for 2-3 min on each side, or until nicely golden and crisp</p><p>Once done, transfer the <strong>golden</strong> <strong>halloumi</strong> to kitchen paper</p>",
      "order": 4,
      "image": "/images/instructions/buffalo-halloumi-with-ranch-dip-and-sweet-potato-fries/step-4.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, heat a pot with 10g <span class=\"text-purple\">[15g]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[20g]</span> <strong>butter</strong> on a low heat</p><p>Once melted, remove the pot from the heat and add your <strong>sriracha </strong>(can't handle the heat? Go easy!),<strong> cider vinegar</strong> and 1 tsp <span class=\"text-purple\">[1 1/2 tsp]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[2 tsp] </span><strong>sugar</strong></p><p>Stir everything together until it combines and becomes a sauce-like consistency – this is your<strong> buffalo sauce</strong></p>",
      "order": 5,
      "image": "/images/instructions/buffalo-halloumi-with-ranch-dip-and-sweet-potato-fries/step-5.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Wash your<strong> lettuce</strong>, pat dry with kitchen paper, then slice<span class=\"text-danger\"> </span>into wedges</p><p>Chop your<strong> chives</strong> finely, then peel and grate your <strong>garlic</strong></p><p>Combine your <strong>natural yoghurt</strong>,<strong> Dijon mustard</strong>, <strong>grated garlic</strong> (not a big garlic fan? Try using less!) and <strong>chopped chives</strong> in a small bowl</p><p>Give everything a good mix up – this is your <strong>ranch dip</strong></p>",
      "order": 6,
      "image": "/images/instructions/buffalo-halloumi-with-ranch-dip-and-sweet-potato-fries/step-6.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Return the <strong>buffalo sauce</strong> pot to a medium heat</p><p>Once hot, add the <strong>golden halloumi</strong> and toss until the halloumi is fully coated in the sauce – this is your <strong>buffalo halloumi</strong></p>",
      "order": 7,
      "image": "/images/instructions/buffalo-halloumi-with-ranch-dip-and-sweet-potato-fries/step-7.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Serve the <strong>buffalo halloumi</strong> with the <strong>sweet potato fries</strong>, <strong>ranch dip</strong> and<strong> lettuce wedges</strong> to the side</p><p>Enjoy!</p>",
      "order": 8
    }
  ],
